Extended Warranty Agreement Market size was valued at USD 130 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 210 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Extended Warranty Agreement Market Overview
The global Extended Warranty Agreement market was valued at approximately USD 120 billion in 2024, and it is projected to reach USD 180 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.5% during the forecast period. The market is driven by increasing consumer demand for product protection plans and the rising costs of repairs for high-end electronics, automotive, and home appliances. This growth is further supported by the rising adoption of extended warranties across various sectors, including automotive, electronics, and consumer goods. Additionally, manufacturers and service providers are continuously introducing innovative products to meet the growing need for after-sales service contracts.

